description:
secretx-aws-kms/src/lib.rs:143-146 allocates 'let mut out = vec![0u8; 64];' (zero-fills 64 bytes) then immediately overwrites both halves with copy_from_slice. Wasted memset.

Suggested rewrite:
  let mut out = Vec::with_capacity(64);
  out.extend_from_slice(&r32);
  out.extend_from_slice(&s32);
  Ok(out)

Or, since the size is fixed:
  let mut out = [0u8; 64];
  out[..32].copy_from_slice(&r32);
  out[32..].copy_from_slice(&s32);
  Ok(out.to_vec())  // single allocation, no zero-fill
(the second form actually re-introduces a zero-fill via to_vec; first form is cleanest)

Effectively cosmetic — 64-byte memset is invisible under network latency. Filed as elegance/idiom. Mark opinion if you disagree.
